# Plex streaming and track URL construction

Apply when editing URL construction for playback, streaming quality, or Plex API/client.

## Song.uri

- Set in `utils/plex-client.ts` (`formatTrack`): direct stream URL with `X-Plex-Token`.
- No bitrate param at Plex client level.

## Quality

- `hooks/usePlaybackSettingsStore.ts` defines `streamingQuality` and `STREAMING_QUALITY_BITRATES`.
- Applied **only** in `songToTrack(song)` in `hooks/useAudioStore.ts`: if URL is not local and not podcast and contains `X-Plex-Token`, append `&maxAudioBitrate=${bitrate}` to get the `url` passed to the native player.

## Single place

- All playback URLs for the player go through `songToTrack()`.
- Do not add quality or token logic in the native module or adapter; keep it in `songToTrack`.

## Prewarm

- The next-track prewarm in useAudioStore uses `nextSong.uri` (no `maxAudioBitrate`).
- Prewarm URL may differ from the quality-limited playback URL; acceptable for cache warming.
